   <a class="btn" href="#card-1"><input type="checkbox">Financial Accounting</a>
   <div class="paragraph">
     <p>This course is an introduction to the 
      basic concepts and standards underlying financial accounting systems.
      Several important concepts will be studied in detail, including: revenue
        recognition, inventory, long-lived assets, present value, and long term 
        liabilities. The course emphasizes the construction of the basic financial 
        accounting statements - the income statement, balance sheet, and cash flow 
        statement - as well as their interpretation.

     </p>
